product: SanDisk - Ultra Dual Drive Go 256GB USB Type-A/USB Type-C Flash Drive - Black
review: The capacity, size, and performance are impressive for this price, but the build quality leaves something to be desired. I've been able to connect it and transfer files reliably to a Windows PC and Galaxy S9 phone, and while the transfer rate wasn't as fast as advertised on the PC, it's because the PC only has slower, first-generation USB 3.0 ports so I'd expect faster performance on a more modern PC. The entire outer housing of the drive is made of plastic, and while it's flexible rather than brittle, since the USB-A connector is also made of this plastic (the USB-C connector is metal), I've been handling it gently. I would not want to leave this tumbling around loosely in a bag or drawer where something heavier might crush it, and I'm being extra careful when inserting or removing it with USB-A ports. I'd have given this 5 stars if not for the plastic USB-A connector.

I've been able to connect it and transfer files reliably to a Windows PC and Galaxy S9 phone, and while the transfer rate wasn't as fast as advertised on the PC, it's because the PC only has slower, first-generation USB 3.0 ports so I'd expect faster performance on a more modern PC. The entire outer housing of the drive is made of plastic, and while it's flexible rather than brittle, since the USB-A connector is also made of this plastic (the USB-C connector is metal), I've been handling it gently. I would not want to leave this tumbling around loosely in a bag or drawer where something heavier might crush it, and I'm being extra careful when inserting or removing it with USB-A ports. I'd have given this 5 stars if not for the plastic USB-A connector.

I've been able to connect it and transfer files reliably to a Windows PC and Galaxy S9 phone, and while the transfer rate wasn't as fast as advertised on the PC, it's because the PC only has slower, first-generation USB 3.0 ports so I'd expect faster performance on a more modern PC. The entire outer housing of the drive is made of plastic, and while it's flexible rather than brittle, since the USB-A connector is also made of this plastic (the USB-C connector is metal), I've been handling it gently. I would not want to leave this tumbling around loosely in a bag or drawer where something heavier might crush it, and I'm being extra careful when inserting or removing it with USB-A ports. I'd have given this 5 stars if not for the plastic USB-A connector.

I've been able to connect it and transfer files reliably to a Windows PC and Galaxy S9 phone, and while the transfer rate wasn't as fast as advertised on the PC, it's because the PC only has slower, first-generation USB 3.0 ports so I'd expect faster performance on a more modern PC. The entire outer housing of the drive is made of plastic, and while it's flexible rather than brittle, since the USB-A connector is also made of this plastic (the USB-C connector is metal), I've been handling it gently. I would not want to leave this tumbling around loosely in a bag or drawer where something heavier might crush it, and I'm being extra careful when inserting or removing it with USB-A ports. I'd have given this 5 stars if not for the plastic USB-A connector.
